    "Page Four TOLEDO UNION JOURNAL Official Publication TolFtfo Industrial Union Certnrcfl ORGANIZE TOLEDO 100 Published every Friday by Local No 12 UAW CIO 425 Hinthrop Street Toledo Ohio Member of American Labor Press Association Editor Melvin Schulte Managing Editor O J record Advertising Manager Burny Zawodny Board of Trustees Melvin Schultz Thomas Burke Randolph Gray SI INSCRIPTION RATES One year by mail in advance Entered at the Toledo Ohio post office as second class matter under the act of Aug 24 1912 Honeymoons End Counting attacks on President Truman by the nations press the industrialist bankers and reactionaries in both major political parties since he advocated in creasing unemployment compensation payments to 25 a week for 26 weeks in dicates beyond all doubt that the Presi dents brief honeymoon with the powers that be is at an end The sniping will now begin in ernest When Mr Truman first assumed tha presidency following the death of Franklin D Roosevelt he was courted not toe subtly by the Republicans reactionary Democrats big business and the press These forces allowing themselves to hope for the best looked at President Trumans background told the nation that he conservative and sat back to wait"
